						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying near the Mosque.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Trailōkyamalla [Sōmēśvara I] 11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is a damaged record in characters of the 11th century A.D. It refers to the rule of Trai(lōkyama)lla, the Chālukya king and to his subordinate <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍḷēśvara</hi> (name lost) who was governing Eḍedoṟe-2000. During this time probably tantrapāla Gangara Chāvuṇḍamayya obtained some lands on his requesting (the king) at [Kalyā]ṇa. The rest is broken and lost.</p>						

						</summary>
